WEBVTT

00:00:55.205 --> 00:00:57.791
How did you get through
what happened between you two?

00:00:58.125 --> 00:01:00.961
Wasn’t it hard?

00:01:01.879 --> 00:01:03.589
Do you regret it?

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:11.236
♪ A glimpse of you in
the middle of the silence. ♪

00:01:11.263 --> 00:01:12.556
What was that?

00:01:13.182 --> 00:01:14.475
You’re writing songs now?

00:01:14.475 --> 00:01:16.935
I think music is
really meant for you.

00:01:17.728 --> 00:01:20.105
Stop forcing me into
your world, Larkin.

00:01:20.272 --> 00:01:21.774
Do you regret meeting me?

00:01:21.857 --> 00:01:23.817
Maybe it would’ve been
better if we never met.

00:01:25.861 --> 00:01:26.612
Via!

00:01:26.612 --> 00:01:27.863
About the beach trip!

00:01:27.863 --> 00:01:29.031
You’re still going, right?

00:01:29.031 --> 00:01:30.783
Of course.
Why wouldn’t I be?

00:01:31.241 --> 00:01:31.950
I’ll get it.

00:01:33.202 --> 00:01:34.328
Put it down first.

00:01:35.662 --> 00:01:36.497
Let go.

00:01:45.839 --> 00:01:47.174
- Via!
- Kino!

00:01:50.302 --> 00:01:52.638
I wonder how long
I’ll be hugged here.

00:01:55.224 --> 00:01:56.016
I’m sorry.

00:01:56.016 --> 00:01:58.060
I didn’t mean what I
said the other day that...

00:01:58.060 --> 00:01:59.853
That maybe I shouldn’t have met you.

00:01:59.895 --> 00:02:00.896
It’s okay, Via.

00:02:01.814 --> 00:02:03.065
I understand.

00:02:05.072 --> 00:02:16.083
♪ May my prayer be heard,
that you answer my plea. ♪

00:02:17.849 --> 00:02:23.938
♪ I find myself smiling again. ♪

00:02:29.252 --> 00:02:30.253
On Saturday,

00:02:30.253 --> 00:02:33.632
I’m going to the construction
site of Clea’s project.

00:02:33.632 --> 00:02:34.532
Want to come?

00:02:35.133 --> 00:02:37.052
I’ll bring the car.

00:02:38.637 --> 00:02:39.551
Let’s go.

00:02:55.904 --> 00:02:57.447
- Let’s go.
- Sure!

00:03:01.868 --> 00:03:02.828
Here it is.

00:03:03.161 --> 00:03:04.037
Clea.

00:03:04.371 --> 00:03:05.539
Let’s focus on work here, okay?

00:03:05.539 --> 00:03:07.082
You might end up
acting like a fanboy later.

00:03:07.082 --> 00:03:08.750
- I’m just smiling because—
- All right, thank you.

00:03:09.501 --> 00:03:10.585
ArClea?

00:03:11.545 --> 00:03:13.046
With your ex, too.

00:03:15.632 --> 00:03:17.175
Hi, Architect Diaz,
you’re here.

00:03:17.175 --> 00:03:18.593
Yeah, hi.

00:03:19.511 --> 00:03:22.180
This is Architect Dan Morales.

00:03:22.597 --> 00:03:25.016
Hi, I’m such a big fan.

00:03:25.392 --> 00:03:27.185
Hi, nice to meet you.

00:03:27.185 --> 00:03:29.688
This is Larkin. Well, you
probably know him.

00:03:29.688 --> 00:03:30.939
Hi, nice meeting you.

00:03:31.481 --> 00:03:32.107
Hi.

00:03:32.399 --> 00:03:33.358
Same here.

00:03:33.358 --> 00:03:35.944
You know, you look familiar.
Have we met before?

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:37.654
I think so.

00:03:37.654 --> 00:03:40.031
Via and I used to be classmates.

00:03:41.241 --> 00:03:42.159
I see.

00:03:44.578 --> 00:03:45.746
Have you eaten?

00:03:45.746 --> 00:03:46.580
I brought food.

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:47.497
- No!
- Not yet.

00:03:47.664 --> 00:03:49.416
No, we’re okay.

00:03:50.709 --> 00:03:53.003
We just stopped by because
I needed to talk to the engineer,

00:03:53.003 --> 00:03:54.254
but we’ll leave right away.

00:03:54.254 --> 00:03:55.172
Right?

00:03:55.380 --> 00:03:56.089
Okay.

00:03:56.673 --> 00:03:57.799
The engineer is over there.

00:03:57.799 --> 00:03:58.759
Yeah. Okay.

00:03:58.759 --> 00:03:59.885
Excuse us.

00:03:59.968 --> 00:04:01.553
Architect Morales, let’s go.

00:04:02.095 --> 00:04:02.929
Alright.

00:04:03.054 --> 00:04:03.889
Okay.

00:04:06.141 --> 00:04:08.101
We’ll leave soon, too, Kino.

00:04:08.101 --> 00:04:09.644
We might be late for the shoot.

00:04:11.605 --> 00:04:12.481
“Kino?”

00:04:14.608 --> 00:04:16.818
I used to be the only one
who called him that.

00:04:17.652 --> 00:04:19.821
Looks like I’ve really been replaced.

00:04:21.239 --> 00:04:22.073
Engineer!

00:04:22.449 --> 00:04:25.827
Hi, this is Architect Dan Morales.
I work with him.

00:04:25.827 --> 00:04:26.912
Hello.

00:04:29.122 --> 00:04:30.290
Via!

00:04:30.290 --> 00:04:31.291
Are you busy?

00:04:32.626 --> 00:04:34.628
Not really. Why did you call?

00:04:36.379 --> 00:04:38.340
Why the long face?

00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:39.633
Huh?

00:04:39.925 --> 00:04:41.426
Nothing. I’m fine.

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:42.844
Nothing?

00:04:43.053 --> 00:04:45.680
I know you too well. Come on, spill it.

00:04:46.681 --> 00:04:48.099
It’s Clea.

00:04:49.017 --> 00:04:52.270
I heard Clea call Arkin, “Kino.”

00:04:55.857 --> 00:04:58.068
It’s not a big deal, maybe...

00:04:58.360 --> 00:04:59.861
Maybe, I’m just being petty.

00:04:59.986 --> 00:05:01.279
What do you mean,
not a big deal?

00:05:01.613 --> 00:05:03.323
That Arkin is such an idiot.

00:05:03.782 --> 00:05:06.243
Weren’t you the only one
who used to call him Kino?

00:05:06.576 --> 00:05:07.702
Yeah.

00:05:08.411 --> 00:05:10.580
But now, I can’t call
him that anymore.

00:05:11.206 --> 00:05:13.208
Are you still affected, Via?

00:05:18.964 --> 00:05:20.841
Maybe not anymore?

00:05:21.258 --> 00:05:22.843
I just keep thinking that...

00:05:23.051 --> 00:05:25.679
if what happened between
us before didn’t happen,

00:05:26.137 --> 00:05:28.014
would we still be okay now?

00:05:28.557 --> 00:05:33.520
Would I still be able to call him
by the nickname that I gave him?

00:05:34.104 --> 00:05:37.607
Because now it feels awkward.

00:05:37.899 --> 00:05:41.570
Even when he’s right there,
I can’t call him that anymore.

00:05:42.362 --> 00:05:43.738
I get it.

00:05:45.156 --> 00:05:47.158
Do you want us to trademark “Kino”

00:05:47.158 --> 00:05:48.910
so you’re the only one
allowed to call him that?

00:05:49.327 --> 00:05:50.245
Luna!

00:05:50.579 --> 00:05:51.913
Don’t be silly.

00:05:52.831 --> 00:05:54.207
All right, see you.

00:05:54.749 --> 00:05:55.792
Love you.

00:05:56.668 --> 00:05:59.129
Okay. Love you.

00:07:26.348 --> 00:07:29.267
- It’s getting chilly here.
- I think I’m getting hungry.

00:07:30.512 --> 00:07:32.347
We’re just going to
prepare some food.

00:07:32.347 --> 00:07:33.798
- Yeah.
- Yeah, that’s right.

00:07:33.969 --> 00:07:35.408
- I’m starving.
- We’ll be back.

00:07:35.433 --> 00:07:36.351
I need to pee.

00:07:36.351 --> 00:07:38.561
- So we’ll just bring you some instead.
- Right.

00:07:38.561 --> 00:07:39.604
- Let’s go.
- Just stay here for now.

00:07:39.604 --> 00:07:41.815
- Yeah, I need to pee.
- Let’s go.

00:08:11.537 --> 00:08:13.101
You have such a beautiful voice.

00:08:15.254 --> 00:08:16.294
Don’t worry.

00:08:16.850 --> 00:08:18.476
I won’t tell you to try again.

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:22.022
But I just want you to know

00:08:23.017 --> 00:08:25.100
that the way I see
your music hasn’t changed.

00:08:28.570 --> 00:08:29.738
Thank you.

00:08:30.822 --> 00:08:31.865
And...

00:08:33.950 --> 00:08:37.829
sorry again for how I reacted.

00:08:39.827 --> 00:08:40.995
It’s fine.

00:08:48.089 --> 00:08:49.080
By the way,

00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:51.875
Mama wants to invite
you to her birthday.

00:08:53.303 --> 00:08:54.763
She’s asking if you’re going.

00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:57.222
It’s just going to be your
family and my family there.

00:08:57.557 --> 00:08:58.895
Your siblings are coming.

00:09:01.227 --> 00:09:04.091
Oh yeah, I heard they already said yes.

00:09:07.242 --> 00:09:09.327
Papa already mentioned it to me.

00:09:09.794 --> 00:09:11.611
It’s a double celebration.

00:09:11.863 --> 00:09:14.824
Mama’s birthday and Arkin’s
mom’s birthday are really close,

00:09:14.824 --> 00:09:16.951
so they always
celebrate them together.

00:09:17.861 --> 00:09:19.404
I don’t have work then.

00:09:19.602 --> 00:09:20.597
Okay.

00:09:20.653 --> 00:09:21.823
I’ll tell Mama.

00:09:26.294 --> 00:09:30.377
Good thing you’re free today.

00:09:33.635 --> 00:09:34.971
I just finished work.

00:09:36.596 --> 00:09:38.987
We finished our last
shooting day for the movie.

00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:44.104
I went straight here
and just slept in the car.

00:09:49.901 --> 00:09:51.459
You take care of yourself.

00:10:03.081 --> 00:10:04.165
Why?

00:10:05.333 --> 00:10:06.350
Nothing.

00:10:07.335 --> 00:10:08.812
I just remembered something.

00:10:12.590 --> 00:10:13.675
Via—

00:10:15.718 --> 00:10:17.549
You’re the one who needs
to take care of yourself.

00:10:19.097 --> 00:10:20.586
Your enemy is yourself.

00:11:11.403 --> 00:11:12.770
Happy Birthday.

00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:25.949
I don’t know what to say to you.

00:11:28.166 --> 00:11:29.870
I’m used to it, though.

00:11:31.336 --> 00:11:33.175
You trained me...

00:11:34.631 --> 00:11:37.175
not to say or feel—

00:11:39.010 --> 00:11:41.192
what I was really
feeling because I still had

00:11:41.216 --> 00:11:43.348
so many things to
take care of in my life.

00:11:52.466 --> 00:11:56.137
Whenever I see kids now,
do you know what I feel?

00:12:01.866 --> 00:12:04.719
I hope they never experience
what I went through.

00:12:08.331 --> 00:12:12.627
I was a child busy taking care
of everyone in the house.

00:12:19.467 --> 00:12:20.551
Other kids

00:12:23.763 --> 00:12:25.556
were happily playing,

00:12:27.558 --> 00:12:29.026
watching cartoons.

00:12:31.020 --> 00:12:32.694
Meanwhile, back then—

00:12:36.901 --> 00:12:39.123
I was watching you lose yourself.

00:12:42.532 --> 00:12:44.748
Watching you drift
away from our family.

00:12:48.162 --> 00:12:49.662
But I had to be there.

00:12:53.001 --> 00:12:54.492
I had to stand up.

00:12:56.546 --> 00:12:58.054
Because you weren’t there anymore.

00:12:59.966 --> 00:13:04.178
I had to be strong, not just
for myself but for my siblings.

00:13:05.013 --> 00:13:07.117
For Ysha, for Mira, for Aidan.

00:13:10.143 --> 00:13:11.477
For Papa.

00:13:18.744 --> 00:13:20.017
I’m angry.

00:13:22.513 --> 00:13:26.200
I’m angry at you because you’re not here
to take all this anger from me.

00:13:28.286 --> 00:13:30.330
I want you to regret

00:13:32.081 --> 00:13:34.876
everything you put me through.

00:13:38.338 --> 00:13:40.515
You made me hate what I love.

00:13:43.217 --> 00:13:46.721
And you forced me
to love what I don’t like.

00:13:51.768 --> 00:13:55.121
You know, before you left...

00:13:57.774 --> 00:14:00.549
I wish you at least made
me feel that you were sorry.

00:14:02.278 --> 00:14:04.355
If I had just heard your apology—

00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:09.620
maybe I wouldn’t have
ended up like this now.

00:14:11.704 --> 00:14:13.879
Because I needed to hear it.

00:14:17.865 --> 00:14:20.484
I wanted to hear you apologize.

00:14:22.799 --> 00:14:25.843
An apology that didn’t
come from Papa,

00:14:28.846 --> 00:14:30.849
not from Arkin,

00:14:33.101 --> 00:14:36.229
not from my siblings.

00:14:39.065 --> 00:14:41.381
An apology coming from you.

00:14:50.410 --> 00:14:52.578
But there’s nothing
I can do anymore.

00:14:54.580 --> 00:14:56.082
You’re gone.

00:14:59.961 --> 00:15:03.464
Maybe I need to ask
forgiveness from myself now.

00:15:06.134 --> 00:15:07.769
And I hope that
when I come back here...

00:15:10.430 --> 00:15:13.933
I hope that when I come back here,
I’ve finally forgiven myself.

00:15:46.257 --> 00:15:46.966
Let’s go.

00:15:46.966 --> 00:15:49.427
- Oh my gosh. It’s so beautiful!
- Wow.

00:15:49.427 --> 00:15:50.344
It’s huge.

00:15:50.369 --> 00:15:51.703
I think it’s here.

00:15:51.971 --> 00:15:53.973
Oh my gosh, I’m so
excited to go swimming!

00:15:53.973 --> 00:15:54.849
Are you guys excited?

00:15:54.849 --> 00:15:55.850
Yeah!

00:15:56.142 --> 00:15:58.060
Oh, my gosh. Let’s hurry!

00:15:59.270 --> 00:16:01.981
- I’m tired.
- I’m so excited.

00:16:03.441 --> 00:16:05.151
Oh, there’s the door.

00:16:06.736 --> 00:16:07.821
Come in.

00:16:08.905 --> 00:16:10.615
It’s so beautiful.

00:16:12.575 --> 00:16:13.451
Hey, Arkin!

00:16:13.451 --> 00:16:15.161
- Arkin!
- Welcome, kids!

00:16:15.161 --> 00:16:15.620
- Arkin!
- Well?

00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:16.496
Let’s go swim.

00:16:16.496 --> 00:16:17.788
Sure!

00:16:18.331 --> 00:16:20.416
- This place is huge.
- It’s so nice.

00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:23.252
I want to go swimming already.

00:16:25.546 --> 00:16:26.923
Hi!

00:16:26.923 --> 00:16:28.508
- Happy birthday, Auntie!
- Happy birthday.

00:16:28.508 --> 00:16:31.052
- Thank you.
- How are you?

00:16:31.052 --> 00:16:34.011
- Papa said he’ll follow later.
- Yeah, I heard.

00:16:34.036 --> 00:16:36.246
- Thank you.
- Happy birthday.

00:16:36.307 --> 00:16:37.725
Via, come!

00:16:37.725 --> 00:16:39.352
You’ve been working nonstop.

00:16:39.352 --> 00:16:40.436
Okay, bye.

00:16:41.395 --> 00:16:42.522
Hi, Auntie.

00:16:42.897 --> 00:16:44.941
- Hi, Auntie.
- Hi.

00:16:45.233 --> 00:16:46.442
Happy birthday.

00:16:46.442 --> 00:16:48.736
I am so happy you’re here.

00:16:48.856 --> 00:16:51.233
My birthday is not
complete without you.

00:16:53.824 --> 00:16:56.369
This is for you. I hope you like it.

00:16:56.369 --> 00:16:57.048
You really didn’t have to.

00:16:57.073 --> 00:16:59.993
Even without a gift,
as long as you’re here, I’m happy.

00:17:02.124 --> 00:17:03.334
Oh, come on. Let’s go.

00:17:03.334 --> 00:17:04.919
Enjoy the pool!

00:17:04.971 --> 00:17:06.046
Swimming!

00:17:06.212 --> 00:17:08.047
Let’s go swimming.
It’s over there...

00:17:08.047 --> 00:17:08.965
You can change there.

00:17:08.965 --> 00:17:09.715
Is it deep?

00:17:09.715 --> 00:17:10.925
Glad you could make it.

00:17:12.843 --> 00:17:14.026
It’s Auntie’s birthday, of course.

00:17:38.786 --> 00:17:40.037
Arkin.

00:17:40.770 --> 00:17:42.365
Come here.

00:17:43.044 --> 00:17:45.567
Kids, come! There’s cake.

00:18:10.776 --> 00:18:12.153
What the heck!

00:18:27.168 --> 00:18:28.711
Come on, smile.

00:18:46.312 --> 00:18:49.143
Want me to take a photo of you?

00:18:50.483 --> 00:18:51.859
Sure.

00:18:52.026 --> 00:18:53.527
Here’s fine.

00:18:55.345 --> 00:18:57.806
How do you want it,
standing or sitting?

00:18:58.028 --> 00:18:59.029
Your choice.

00:18:59.356 --> 00:19:00.720
Okay, this should do for now.

00:19:11.813 --> 00:19:12.939
I’ll stand now.

00:19:22.056 --> 00:19:23.015
Your turn.

00:19:23.015 --> 00:19:23.474
Me?

00:19:23.474 --> 00:19:24.725
Yeah, it's your turn.

00:19:25.309 --> 00:19:26.290
Your turn now.

00:19:27.812 --> 00:19:28.730
Ready—

00:19:35.361 --> 00:19:36.195
Stay here.

00:19:36.195 --> 00:19:38.656
You’re against the light.

00:19:42.284 --> 00:19:43.146
Ready?

00:19:52.082 --> 00:19:53.626
So pretty.

00:19:54.004 --> 00:19:55.339
What did you say?

00:20:01.862 --> 00:20:05.366
Let’s take a group
picture as a remembrance.

00:20:05.391 --> 00:20:06.475
Yeah, that’s right.

00:20:06.684 --> 00:20:07.727
Sure, come on.

00:20:07.727 --> 00:20:08.644
Come here.

00:20:08.644 --> 00:20:09.437
Let’s go, Via.

00:20:16.444 --> 00:20:17.214
Okay.

00:20:17.737 --> 00:20:20.781
Arkin, Via, can you
move closer together?

00:20:20.781 --> 00:20:23.242
So that we’ll all fit in the frame.

00:20:23.242 --> 00:20:23.868
Okay.

00:20:23.868 --> 00:20:25.077
- Let’s just sit by the edge.
- Okay.

00:20:25.077 --> 00:20:25.995
Closer.

00:20:26.078 --> 00:20:27.204
Move closer.

00:20:30.166 --> 00:20:31.333
Come on, closer.

00:20:31.667 --> 00:20:33.002
There you go.

00:20:33.002 --> 00:20:36.505
We all fit in the frame.

00:20:37.715 --> 00:20:39.008
Okay, all done.

00:20:51.312 --> 00:20:52.396
There you go.

00:20:52.480 --> 00:20:54.398
Can you get the
food in the kitchen, please?

00:20:54.398 --> 00:20:56.025
- Yes, ma’am.
- Thank you.

00:20:56.025 --> 00:20:56.776
Hold on.

00:20:56.776 --> 00:20:58.611
Thank you, girls.

00:20:59.737 --> 00:21:01.405
What’s happening there?

00:21:02.948 --> 00:21:03.991
You know, Via,

00:21:05.159 --> 00:21:08.579
I kind of feel sorry for whoever
becomes Arkin’s next girlfriend.

00:21:09.288 --> 00:21:10.748
Huh? Why?

00:21:10.748 --> 00:21:12.416
And don’t say that.

00:21:12.416 --> 00:21:15.294
What if he already has a girlfriend
and you’re making her sound pitiful?

00:21:16.337 --> 00:21:19.548
Because it’s you that
his family keeps looking for.

00:21:19.924 --> 00:21:22.134
Our families are really close.

00:21:23.260 --> 00:21:28.140
If I were the new girlfriend,
I don’t think I could handle that.

00:21:29.225 --> 00:21:31.852
Maybe that’s why Arkin still
doesn’t have a new girlfriend yet.

00:21:36.649 --> 00:21:38.859
We’re not even sure about that.

00:21:38.984 --> 00:21:40.694
And if he does,

00:21:40.694 --> 00:21:42.363
I’ll be the one to step back.

00:21:42.363 --> 00:21:44.615
I’ll be the one to keep
my distance out of respect.

00:21:50.120 --> 00:21:52.873
Go ahead and fix the plates.
I’ll take care of the glasses.

00:21:53.022 --> 00:21:54.032
Okay.

00:21:58.263 --> 00:22:00.182
I wonder if he
already has a girlfriend?

00:22:04.885 --> 00:22:06.512
Are he and Clea together now?

00:22:12.598 --> 00:22:13.974
I want spring rolls.

00:22:14.728 --> 00:22:16.689
She wants spring rolls.

00:22:16.897 --> 00:22:20.401
- Here, serve me since it’s my birthday.
- Of course, mother.

00:22:21.735 --> 00:22:22.361
One more.

00:22:22.361 --> 00:22:23.462
One more?

00:22:23.487 --> 00:22:24.601
Thank you.

00:22:24.947 --> 00:22:25.656
You should eat, too, dear.

00:22:25.656 --> 00:22:26.567
All right.

00:22:26.907 --> 00:22:27.633
Chicken, hon?

00:22:27.658 --> 00:22:28.242
I’m okay.

00:22:28.242 --> 00:22:30.411
I’m happy with my spring rolls.

00:22:36.250 --> 00:22:37.459
Thank you, Arkin.

00:22:42.172 --> 00:22:43.291
Thank you.

00:22:43.382 --> 00:22:44.884
Thanks, Arkin.

00:22:44.884 --> 00:22:46.045
So delicious.

00:22:48.888 --> 00:22:50.347
He really doesn’t miss a beat

00:22:50.347 --> 00:22:52.366
when it comes to taking
care of my family.

00:22:56.353 --> 00:22:59.023
It’s like second nature to him now.

00:23:09.591 --> 00:23:10.774
Is it okay?

00:23:16.498 --> 00:23:17.625
Of course.

00:23:19.293 --> 00:23:20.502
It’s all chicken skin.

00:23:20.542 --> 00:23:21.668
Actually, their chicken is really good.

00:23:21.792 --> 00:23:23.919
You still don’t eat this?

00:23:29.637 --> 00:23:30.804
Do you want some rice?

00:23:38.312 --> 00:23:40.648
I’m jealous. Me too, serve me.

00:23:57.915 --> 00:23:59.833
I’m so happy she’s here.

00:24:00.042 --> 00:24:01.168
Let me help you.

00:24:01.168 --> 00:24:02.378
No need, sir. I can manage.

00:24:02.378 --> 00:24:03.396
Okay, then.

00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:12.593
Still working?

00:24:20.813 --> 00:24:22.189
You okay?

00:24:22.606 --> 00:24:24.191
What’s on your mind?

00:24:27.736 --> 00:24:29.446
A lot.

00:24:32.241 --> 00:24:35.452
Then tell me everything.

00:24:38.747 --> 00:24:41.250
Did you post your pictures?

00:24:43.085 --> 00:24:44.378
No.

00:24:46.296 --> 00:24:49.216
I was trying to avoid everything
that would link back to you.

00:24:49.216 --> 00:24:50.718
It’s hard.

00:24:53.929 --> 00:24:58.600
Is it hard for you, or for me?

00:25:01.097 --> 00:25:02.101
Both.

00:25:04.273 --> 00:25:07.776
It’s hard for me
because it’s hard for you.

00:25:12.614 --> 00:25:14.685
I visited Mama yesterday.

00:25:16.910 --> 00:25:19.626
There’s so much I
still want to tell her, but—

00:25:20.497 --> 00:25:26.378
I wonder, if what happened
to her hadn’t happened,

00:25:26.378 --> 00:25:28.297
if she hadn’t gone through all that—

00:25:33.761 --> 00:25:35.846
Would we still be okay now?

00:25:44.646 --> 00:25:46.523
That was my mistake, Via.

00:25:48.150 --> 00:25:55.199
I never wanted you
to end up in that situation.

00:25:58.869 --> 00:26:00.248
But I failed.

00:26:00.835 --> 00:26:02.002
I failed you.

00:26:03.290 --> 00:26:04.508
That was my fault.

00:26:09.838 --> 00:26:11.799
Until now, I’m still not okay.

00:26:16.178 --> 00:26:18.388
No matter how many years pass,

00:26:22.241 --> 00:26:23.926
I’m still not okay.

00:26:27.395 --> 00:26:29.096
You’re so hard to forget.

00:26:31.068 --> 00:26:32.611
How could I ever forget you?

00:26:32.611 --> 00:26:36.288
No matter where I go,
no matter where I look,

00:26:38.742 --> 00:26:40.141
I see you.

00:26:45.249 --> 00:26:47.453
Is it even possible to forget you?

00:26:49.419 --> 00:26:50.546
How about you?

00:26:52.722 --> 00:26:54.266
Even—

00:26:57.219 --> 00:26:58.660
Even once—

00:27:01.723 --> 00:27:03.786
did you ever think of forgetting me?

00:27:10.899 --> 00:27:12.151
Via.

00:27:16.572 --> 00:27:21.243
No matter how painful it was
waking up and finding you gone,

00:27:22.119 --> 00:27:26.373
I never wished to forget you.

00:27:29.042 --> 00:27:30.210
How could I?

00:27:31.253 --> 00:27:32.546
When you were my beginning.

00:27:34.756 --> 00:27:36.717
From the very start,
you were there.

00:27:39.928 --> 00:27:42.556
You supported me throughout my life.

00:27:44.433 --> 00:27:46.810
You made me love music
because you couldn’t.

00:27:48.122 --> 00:27:51.083
You made me pursue music
for you because you couldn’t.

00:27:53.108 --> 00:27:55.694
I took the spotlight
because you couldn’t.

00:28:01.867 --> 00:28:05.286
The only time I can truly love
music is when it comes from you.

00:28:07.206 --> 00:28:08.696
When I see you

00:28:10.876 --> 00:28:12.753
pursue what I couldn’t.

00:28:16.006 --> 00:28:17.705
When I see you in love

00:28:21.011 --> 00:28:23.397
with what I also
fell in love with once.

00:28:36.652 --> 00:28:38.987
You’re still my music, Via.

00:28:39.869 --> 00:28:42.038
So how could I ever forget you?

00:28:46.787 --> 00:28:47.996
I’m sorry.

00:28:51.083 --> 00:28:54.503
I’m sorry I wasn’t brave
enough to take everything in.

00:28:57.172 --> 00:29:00.342
I’m sorry for leaving you
without saying anything.

00:29:03.804 --> 00:29:07.266
I’m sorry I didn’t look back
when I heard you call my name.

00:29:10.560 --> 00:29:12.521
Please, don’t say sorry.

00:29:15.065 --> 00:29:20.028
Why are you saying sorry
for protecting your peace?

00:29:22.447 --> 00:29:26.952
To be honest, I was mad at you.

00:29:28.083 --> 00:29:30.013
I was really mad at you, Via.

00:29:31.588 --> 00:29:34.110
But still, I understood.

00:29:35.127 --> 00:29:37.560
I also needed to keep
my distance from you.

00:29:38.588 --> 00:29:40.799
Because I might not
be able to stop myself

00:29:41.991 --> 00:29:43.291
from hugging you.

00:29:45.618 --> 00:29:47.357
In a way, we’re like magnets.

00:29:48.557 --> 00:29:52.060
I’ll always be drawn to you
whenever you’re near.

00:29:54.021 --> 00:29:57.311
We always find our way back
to each other, you know that.

00:30:04.614 --> 00:30:07.031
Do you think we can
bring our friendship back?

00:30:11.121 --> 00:30:12.211
We could try.

00:30:14.207 --> 00:30:17.854
If you also let me help you
figure out what you really want.

00:30:22.049 --> 00:30:23.468
I know what I want.

00:30:27.804 --> 00:30:29.264
It’s just that I can’t.

00:30:30.682 --> 00:30:32.225
You can, Via.

00:30:34.102 --> 00:30:35.438
Because I’m here.

00:30:36.521 --> 00:30:38.106
I’ll be with you.

00:30:40.359 --> 00:30:45.113
Until all the anger and
pain in your heart are gone,

00:30:45.989 --> 00:30:47.824
until you’re okay...

00:30:51.328 --> 00:30:52.996
I promised, remember?

00:30:54.873 --> 00:30:56.708
I won’t leave you alone.

00:31:09.554 --> 00:31:10.806
It’s okay.

00:31:12.474 --> 00:31:14.393
You have me.

00:31:14.518 --> 00:31:16.186
Always.

00:31:18.397 --> 00:31:20.232
Until you’re okay

00:31:21.566 --> 00:31:23.902
until you’re ready to live again.

00:31:25.445 --> 00:31:27.239
I’ll always be right behind you.

00:32:04.359 --> 00:32:06.653
Via, Arkin! Let’s go swimming.

00:32:06.653 --> 00:32:07.612
Come on.

00:32:09.739 --> 00:32:10.949
Let’s go.

00:32:48.653 --> 00:32:50.572
I forgot to send this.

00:33:03.627 --> 00:33:08.173
Who’s making you smile
like that, Architect Diaz?

00:33:08.173 --> 00:33:10.550
You have a
boyfriend now, don’t you?

00:33:10.550 --> 00:33:11.843
Huh?

00:33:11.968 --> 00:33:14.888
A boyfriend? No, I don’t have one.

00:33:14.888 --> 00:33:15.722
Are you sure?

00:33:15.722 --> 00:33:17.516
You seem to be glowing more lately.

00:33:17.516 --> 00:33:18.808
- So true.
- Right?

00:33:18.808 --> 00:33:20.227
Your smile’s different.

00:33:20.435 --> 00:33:24.164
Well, maybe I’m just naturally pretty.

00:33:24.189 --> 00:33:25.398
Anyway, back to work now.

00:33:25.398 --> 00:33:27.609
- All right.
- We’ll go ahead now.

00:33:33.573 --> 00:33:36.243
Ever since Arkin and I
talked at the resort,

00:33:36.451 --> 00:33:39.162
it feels like our friendship
is slowly coming back.

00:33:39.412 --> 00:33:41.748
Arkin also texts me all the time now.

00:33:44.209 --> 00:33:47.813
Even about the most random things.

00:33:57.795 --> 00:33:59.213
Do you want breakfast?

00:34:00.350 --> 00:34:02.538
Texting me at 4am already?

00:34:07.148 --> 00:34:08.108
No, thanks.

00:34:08.108 --> 00:34:10.151
And why are you up so early?

00:34:22.622 --> 00:34:23.957
Here. Take this with you.

00:34:23.957 --> 00:34:25.292
Eat already, Via.

00:34:25.417 --> 00:34:26.719
- Huh?
- Thank you.

00:34:27.919 --> 00:34:30.672
Via, Arkin brought so much food.

00:34:31.089 --> 00:34:32.507
It’s all delicious.

00:34:33.592 --> 00:34:34.884
I’ll get your food ready.

00:34:34.884 --> 00:34:35.510
Sit down.

00:34:35.510 --> 00:34:38.221
You’re already here?
I just sent my reply to you.

00:34:39.097 --> 00:34:42.225
I texted you, but you didn’t reply,
so I thought you were still sleeping.

00:34:42.565 --> 00:34:44.984
So just to be safe, I brought breakfast.

00:34:50.275 --> 00:34:51.693
We’ll go now, Via.

00:34:51.693 --> 00:34:53.111
- Bye.
- Huh? Oh, okay. Take care.

00:34:53.111 --> 00:34:54.571
- Take care on your way.
- Bye, Arkin.

00:34:54.571 --> 00:34:55.822
- Take care.
- Stay safe.

00:34:55.822 --> 00:34:57.449
- Be good, okay?
- Bye, Via.

00:34:57.449 --> 00:34:58.950
Study hard. Bye, take care.

00:35:05.749 --> 00:35:07.125
What time did you get here?

00:35:08.585 --> 00:35:10.378
Around 5:30, I think.

00:35:11.338 --> 00:35:12.547
I missed it.

00:35:13.465 --> 00:35:14.482
Huh?

00:35:15.300 --> 00:35:20.889
The breakfast, this, the...

00:35:20.889 --> 00:35:22.057
breakfast.

00:35:23.308 --> 00:35:24.142
I thought...

00:35:24.225 --> 00:35:26.102
I thought you meant
something else you missed.

00:35:26.886 --> 00:35:27.787
Via—

00:35:27.812 --> 00:35:28.715
Yeah?

00:35:29.091 --> 00:35:32.132
My new movie is showing soon.

00:35:33.652 --> 00:35:35.933
Of course, we’ll all watch it.

00:35:36.363 --> 00:35:39.658
Of course, as your
friends, we’ll support you.

00:35:41.576 --> 00:35:42.535
Thanks.

00:35:43.203 --> 00:35:44.383
Eat now.

00:35:44.408 --> 00:35:45.993
So you can get going.

00:35:46.247 --> 00:35:47.415
Here, some tocino.

00:35:48.500 --> 00:35:50.710
- You eat, too, okay?
- Yeah, sure.

00:35:53.536 --> 00:35:55.580
- Just a little rice?
- Yeah, just a little.

00:35:57.926 --> 00:35:59.135
That’s enough, thank you.

00:36:00.106 --> 00:36:00.856
Eat now.

00:36:00.881 --> 00:36:01.966
You, too.

00:36:17.320 --> 00:36:19.447
Do you want coffee? Food?

00:36:20.281 --> 00:36:22.534
I’m still at the site. Working.

00:36:26.705 --> 00:36:29.082
All right. What time are you going home?

00:36:30.458 --> 00:36:32.460
Maybe later.

00:36:35.880 --> 00:36:39.134
Via, you’ve been
looking pale since earlier.

00:36:40.719 --> 00:36:41.761
Have you eaten?

00:36:41.761 --> 00:36:42.762
Do you want a sandwich?

00:36:42.762 --> 00:36:44.055
No, I’m okay.

00:36:45.306 --> 00:36:46.266
I also need to leave soon

00:36:46.266 --> 00:36:49.060
because I have a video
meeting with my firm in Spain.

00:36:49.477 --> 00:36:50.228
Okay.

00:36:50.854 --> 00:36:52.272
But are you sure you’re really okay?

00:36:52.272 --> 00:36:54.315
Yeah, I’m okay. Don’t worry.

00:36:55.817 --> 00:36:59.904
Looks like it’s going
to rain. Shall we go?

00:37:00.050 --> 00:37:01.531
Okay. Let’s go.

00:37:12.834 --> 00:37:13.668
Via.

00:37:13.752 --> 00:37:16.629
Oh. What are you
doing here again?

00:37:17.046 --> 00:37:18.339
I brought you some food.

00:37:18.339 --> 00:37:19.299
Go ahead.

00:37:24.304 --> 00:37:25.680
What happened to you?

00:37:25.972 --> 00:37:27.390
You look so pale.

00:37:27.515 --> 00:37:28.391
It’s nothing.

00:37:29.100 --> 00:37:30.602
You’re running hot.

00:37:30.602 --> 00:37:31.603
Come here.

00:37:31.728 --> 00:37:33.772
I’ll prepare your
food so you can rest.

00:37:34.522 --> 00:37:36.524
I’m fine. I’ll eat later.

00:37:37.150 --> 00:37:38.401
What do you mean?

00:37:38.401 --> 00:37:40.653
You need to eat
to fill yourself up.

00:37:41.321 --> 00:37:45.575
Then take medicine later so
you don’t end up with a fever.

00:37:46.326 --> 00:37:47.160
Yeah.

00:37:47.660 --> 00:37:50.038
It’s because the weather’s
been changing a lot lately.

00:37:50.330 --> 00:37:52.540
Take care of yourself, Via.

00:37:52.916 --> 00:37:54.959
Drink water all the time
so you don’t get dehydrated,

00:37:54.959 --> 00:37:58.880
and bring an umbrella so
you won’t get wet if it rains.

00:37:59.923 --> 00:38:01.883
Eat already, you’re so stubborn.

00:38:03.760 --> 00:38:05.220
You’re the one being stubborn.

00:38:05.720 --> 00:38:08.014
I’m so tired from work,
and you’re still bothering me.

00:38:08.014 --> 00:38:08.765
You’re so pushy.

00:38:08.765 --> 00:38:10.433
Call me pushy all you want,

00:38:10.433 --> 00:38:13.603
but I’d rather be that than have
you feel worse than you already do.

00:38:13.603 --> 00:38:14.687
Now, eat.

00:38:15.271 --> 00:38:16.564
Eat plenty.

00:38:17.190 --> 00:38:18.316
I have medicine here.

00:38:21.653 --> 00:38:22.743
Here.

00:38:22.946 --> 00:38:24.948
Take this after you eat, okay?

00:38:24.948 --> 00:38:26.449
Then rest right after.

00:38:26.674 --> 00:38:29.636
Don’t use your phone
anymore so you can sleep early.

00:38:29.661 --> 00:38:30.787
All right.

00:38:31.204 --> 00:38:32.293
Okay.

00:38:32.419 --> 00:38:33.587
What do you want, this one?

00:38:34.082 --> 00:38:35.375
There’s still some chicken here.

00:38:35.375 --> 00:38:37.627
You eat, too. Let’s eat together.

00:38:45.134 --> 00:38:46.427
You still have a report, Via.

00:38:46.427 --> 00:38:47.929
You need to go to work.

00:38:57.313 --> 00:39:00.400
Take this before lunch,
don’t skip meals! - Kino

00:39:01.192 --> 00:39:04.864
It’s just like before. I used to
be the one doing this for him.

00:39:05.478 --> 00:39:06.145
Via?

00:39:06.239 --> 00:39:07.740
Got any extra eggs there?

00:39:07.740 --> 00:39:09.367
Of course, I already
added an extra egg.

00:39:09.367 --> 00:39:10.743
I know it’s your favorite.

00:39:11.536 --> 00:39:13.246
Wow, you’re the best, Via!

00:39:13.246 --> 00:39:14.956
That’s why you’re my best friend.

00:39:26.162 --> 00:39:29.665
You really put in a lot of effort, huh?

00:39:45.120 --> 00:39:46.821
Is this finished?

00:39:46.821 --> 00:39:48.406
It’s finished, Architect.

00:39:48.406 --> 00:39:49.699
Yes, it’s done.

00:39:50.304 --> 00:39:53.286
All right, have lunch first
before you start the next task.

00:39:53.543 --> 00:39:54.920
Okay. Let’s go, guys.

00:39:54.996 --> 00:39:57.081
Architect, are you going to eat?

00:39:57.081 --> 00:39:58.057
I’ll eat later.

00:39:58.082 --> 00:39:58.979
Thank you.

00:40:04.422 --> 00:40:06.591
All right, I’ll work on it.

00:40:10.553 --> 00:40:11.679
Why did you still come in?

00:40:11.679 --> 00:40:13.389
You should’ve just taken a sick leave.

00:40:15.892 --> 00:40:17.101
I’m okay.

00:40:17.477 --> 00:40:20.647
I’ll just finish this,
then I’ll go home early.

00:40:21.314 --> 00:40:23.816
Okay, but if you need
anything, tell me, all right?

00:40:23.816 --> 00:40:26.027
Sure. Thank you.

00:40:31.032 --> 00:40:32.034
Let’s fix this, okay?

00:40:40.833 --> 00:40:41.584
Hello?

00:40:42.540 --> 00:40:44.042
How are you feeling?

00:40:45.463 --> 00:40:49.467
I’m feeling a bit better now.
What you left really helped.

00:40:49.467 --> 00:40:51.177
Thanks again.

00:40:52.011 --> 00:40:54.138
You’re welcome.
Don’t skip meals, okay?

00:40:55.431 --> 00:40:56.432
Okay.

00:40:57.517 --> 00:40:58.267
I need to go.

00:40:58.267 --> 00:41:00.770
We’re about to shoot. Get well soon.

00:41:01.020 --> 00:41:03.481
Yeah, thanks.

00:41:13.574 --> 00:41:17.370
Want to eat out
with me and Ke? I’m sad.

00:41:22.583 --> 00:41:25.253
You know, I’m happy that
you and Arkin are talking again.

00:41:25.406 --> 00:41:26.448
Right.

00:41:26.587 --> 00:41:30.091
What’s important is that your
friendship is coming back.

00:41:30.550 --> 00:41:32.802
You’ve been friends for longer

00:41:32.802 --> 00:41:34.887
than the time you distanced
yourselves from each other.

00:41:36.305 --> 00:41:37.306
Yeah, that’s true.

00:41:41.185 --> 00:41:42.228
Are you okay?

00:41:43.195 --> 00:41:44.071
Let me see.

00:41:45.690 --> 00:41:46.983
You’re warm.

00:41:47.567 --> 00:41:49.485
Why did you still come here?

00:41:49.819 --> 00:41:53.072
I’m fine, and besides,
you said you were sad, right?

00:41:53.156 --> 00:41:55.825
That’s why I came. I can handle it.

00:41:55.992 --> 00:41:58.119
You should go home
now so you can rest.

00:41:59.084 --> 00:42:00.576
Did you bring a car?

00:42:00.705 --> 00:42:01.873
No, I just booked a ride.

00:42:02.081 --> 00:42:03.016
Huh?

00:42:03.041 --> 00:42:04.292
Oh, I’ll message Arkin.

00:42:04.417 --> 00:42:05.710
Hey, don’t.

00:42:05.710 --> 00:42:06.961
It’s fine.

00:42:12.925 --> 00:42:14.802
Oh, it’s Dan!

00:42:15.136 --> 00:42:16.054
- Dan!
- Luna, Kierra.

00:42:16.054 --> 00:42:17.305
Hey, Dan, long time no see.

00:42:17.305 --> 00:42:18.556
- Why are you here?
- Oh. You’re here too?

00:42:18.731 --> 00:42:20.593
I have a meeting with a friend of mine.

00:42:20.683 --> 00:42:21.517
Are they here now?

00:42:21.517 --> 00:42:23.269
No, I’m thirty minutes early.

00:42:23.269 --> 00:42:24.484
Sit down first, sit down.

00:42:24.854 --> 00:42:26.022
- Oh—
- All right

00:42:26.314 --> 00:42:28.024
Did I tell you
that we work together?

00:42:28.107 --> 00:42:29.525
- No. Really?
- Yes.

00:42:29.525 --> 00:42:30.860
Why don’t you order first?

00:42:30.860 --> 00:42:31.778
Yeah, eat with us.

00:42:31.778 --> 00:42:33.654
- All right.
- Yes. Let’s order.

00:42:36.783 --> 00:42:39.535
You know, I was
starstruck when I first saw Clea.

00:42:39.535 --> 00:42:41.871
She really looks great in person.

00:42:42.205 --> 00:42:44.582
She looks like an angel
sent down from heaven.

00:42:46.542 --> 00:42:49.462
By the way, Dan. Doesn’t Clea
already have a boyfriend?

00:42:49.462 --> 00:42:51.297
Yes, I heard.

00:42:51.297 --> 00:42:53.007
Not Arkin, though.

00:42:53.132 --> 00:42:54.634
Hey, Luna.

00:42:54.759 --> 00:42:55.384
Why?

00:42:55.384 --> 00:42:57.095
How do you even know that?

00:42:57.095 --> 00:43:01.099
Don’t gossip about it to others,
especially when it’s not confirmed.

00:43:01.140 --> 00:43:02.809
All right, I’ll verify it.

00:43:02.809 --> 00:43:04.644
But it doesn’t really
seem like gossip.

00:43:05.853 --> 00:43:07.188
Do you remember Victor?

00:43:07.188 --> 00:43:07.897
Yeah, I do.

00:43:07.897 --> 00:43:10.650
It’s just that Victor, our co-worker—

00:43:10.650 --> 00:43:12.527
Oh, he’s your co-worker—

00:43:12.527 --> 00:43:14.112
- Then—
- Hey, Arkin’s here.

00:43:18.199 --> 00:43:19.325
Hi.

00:43:20.618 --> 00:43:22.078
How are you?

00:43:22.537 --> 00:43:23.538
I’m good.

00:43:27.166 --> 00:43:29.210
Via, let’s go?

00:43:29.544 --> 00:43:31.170
You’re not well yet.
Let’s go home.

00:43:31.337 --> 00:43:33.381
Don’t you want to eat first?
We can order.

00:43:33.381 --> 00:43:35.049
I’m fine. I’m full, thanks.

00:43:35.633 --> 00:43:36.498
Let’s go?

00:43:37.969 --> 00:43:38.886
We’ll go ahead.

00:43:38.886 --> 00:43:39.428
All right.

00:43:39.428 --> 00:43:40.471
- Take care, you two.
- Okay.

00:43:40.471 --> 00:43:42.181
I’ll just keep my distance,
wouldn’t wanna catch anything.

00:43:42.181 --> 00:43:43.015
Yeah, all right.

00:43:43.015 --> 00:43:43.724
- Hey!
- Be careful on the road.

00:43:43.724 --> 00:43:45.518
- Via, here’s some vitamins.
- Yeah?

00:43:46.018 --> 00:43:48.187
You looked pale earlier at the office.

00:43:48.437 --> 00:43:49.897
I was going to give
them to you tomorrow.

00:43:52.400 --> 00:43:53.609
Thanks.

00:43:54.861 --> 00:43:55.945
- Okay.
- All right.

00:43:56.445 --> 00:43:57.655
- Take care.
- Okay. Arkin—

00:43:57.655 --> 00:43:58.531
- Just update us.
- Bye!

00:43:58.531 --> 00:43:59.949
- When you both get home.
- All right.

00:43:59.949 --> 00:44:00.863
Come on.

00:44:02.451 --> 00:44:03.452
Via?

00:44:03.744 --> 00:44:05.288
- Oh my god!
- Damn it...

00:44:05.288 --> 00:44:06.205
Pres!

00:44:06.998 --> 00:44:07.906
- Larkin!
- Pres.

00:44:07.999 --> 00:44:08.916
How have you been?

00:44:08.916 --> 00:44:10.184
You’re famous now!

00:44:10.209 --> 00:44:10.793
Pres!

00:44:10.793 --> 00:44:11.711
Come on here.

00:44:11.711 --> 00:44:13.337
- Pres.
- Pres!

00:44:13.337 --> 00:44:14.547
Long time no see.

00:44:14.547 --> 00:44:17.175
Oh my god. How are you guys?

00:44:17.258 --> 00:44:18.134
Kierra!

00:44:18.176 --> 00:44:19.677
Why are you here?

00:44:19.677 --> 00:44:22.221
Pres and I ran into each other
the other day at an event.

00:44:22.221 --> 00:44:23.190
And now you’re here.

00:44:23.309 --> 00:44:24.532
Small world.

00:44:24.557 --> 00:44:26.517
Pres, do you remember Via?

00:44:26.642 --> 00:44:29.979
Do you remember the girl who
confessed to you back in high school—

00:44:29.979 --> 00:44:31.647
You’re in Manila now, Pres?

00:44:32.373 --> 00:44:34.458
No, not really.
I still work with FlyAsia.

00:44:34.483 --> 00:44:35.610
- Ah, FlyAsia.
- I just had a meeting there earlier,

00:44:35.610 --> 00:44:38.070
- that’s why I ended up here.
- Oh, okay, a meeting.

00:44:38.070 --> 00:44:41.490
I thought you met
up with your partner.

00:44:42.116 --> 00:44:42.950
Why?

00:44:42.992 --> 00:44:43.743
We broke up.

00:44:43.826 --> 00:44:44.911
What? Really?

00:44:44.911 --> 00:44:45.887
We broke up.

00:44:45.912 --> 00:44:47.496
- Are you okay, Pres?
- I’m okay.

00:44:47.496 --> 00:44:49.123
Sorry about my cousin here.

00:44:49.123 --> 00:44:51.542
It’s just that she
can’t hold her tongue.

00:44:51.542 --> 00:44:52.293
We don’t have to talk about it.

00:44:52.293 --> 00:44:53.628
It’s okay. Don’t worry about it.

00:44:55.004 --> 00:44:55.922
Wait—

00:44:56.464 --> 00:44:57.465
Via, are you okay?

00:44:57.590 --> 00:44:58.549
You look sick.

00:44:58.758 --> 00:45:01.385
She’s not feeling well,
that’s why we’re going home.

00:45:02.600 --> 00:45:03.346
- Get well...
- All right.

00:45:03.346 --> 00:45:04.430
Get well soon, okay?

00:45:04.782 --> 00:45:05.699
All right, we’ll go ahead.

00:45:05.973 --> 00:45:06.974
- All right, Pres.
- Okay. Take care.

00:45:06.974 --> 00:45:07.934
- Rest well, okay?
- Bye.

00:45:07.934 --> 00:45:08.976
Next time then.

00:45:09.143 --> 00:45:10.311
We’ll see you around, guys.

00:45:10.394 --> 00:45:11.418
Bye.

00:45:13.998 --> 00:45:15.458
- Pres, eat with us for a bit.
- What’s going on there?

00:45:15.483 --> 00:45:16.332
Pres, it seems...

00:45:16.359 --> 00:45:18.569
Pres, have you noticed? I grew taller.

00:45:18.778 --> 00:45:20.071
We’re about the same height now.

00:45:20.988 --> 00:45:22.907
Ah, really? Really now?

00:45:22.907 --> 00:45:23.741
Pres, sit here.

00:45:23.741 --> 00:45:25.743
- Is that really what you have to say?
- Sit beside me.

00:45:32.458 --> 00:45:34.210
Are you still going to work?

00:45:36.629 --> 00:45:38.798
Maybe not. I already
asked to take a leave.

00:45:39.548 --> 00:45:42.677
And my boss saw
that I’m sick anyway.

00:45:45.638 --> 00:45:46.514
What about you?

00:45:46.639 --> 00:45:48.391
Do you have a schedule tomorrow?

00:45:48.516 --> 00:45:49.976
Do you have work?

00:45:50.434 --> 00:45:51.477
In the afternoon.

00:46:13.207 --> 00:46:14.458
How are things with you and Dan?

00:46:16.085 --> 00:46:18.129
That’s so random.

00:46:18.129 --> 00:46:19.922
Why is he asking about Dan and me?

00:46:22.521 --> 00:46:23.897
We’re okay, I guess.

00:46:25.142 --> 00:46:28.103
We’re fine. He’s a good co-worker.

00:46:34.478 --> 00:46:36.397
It’s been a while
since I saw Pres.

00:46:36.696 --> 00:46:37.540
Oh.

00:46:37.565 --> 00:46:38.566
What about it?

00:46:39.563 --> 00:46:41.190
You’re not his crush.

00:46:43.321 --> 00:46:45.114
I never said I was his crush.

00:46:45.139 --> 00:46:46.598
Jeez.

00:46:47.325 --> 00:46:48.428
Churros?

00:46:50.953 --> 00:46:52.330
I like you.

00:46:54.290 --> 00:46:55.458
Thank you, Via.

00:46:56.334 --> 00:46:57.418
Want some churros?

00:47:00.171 --> 00:47:02.256
They broke up, huh?

00:47:02.965 --> 00:47:04.425
What a shame.

00:47:05.092 --> 00:47:06.469
He looks good, right?

00:47:08.919 --> 00:47:09.628
Yeah.

00:47:10.473 --> 00:47:12.266
But it’s still a shame,

00:47:12.266 --> 00:47:14.631
he was a good match for his ex.

00:47:21.984 --> 00:47:24.653
I just hope all will be well for them.

00:47:24.653 --> 00:47:28.157
At least, things are getting
better for Kino and me.

00:47:42.296 --> 00:47:43.263
It’s high.

00:47:46.164 --> 00:47:47.248
You’re really warm.

00:47:49.970 --> 00:47:51.764
Here. Take this medicine.

00:47:56.750 --> 00:47:57.792
Hold this.

00:47:58.687 --> 00:48:02.858
And also these
vitamins that Dan gave you.

00:48:21.127 --> 00:48:23.129
I’m puzzled by how he acts.

00:48:23.963 --> 00:48:26.006
But I guess that’s how friends are.

00:48:26.549 --> 00:48:27.550
It’s okay!

00:48:27.550 --> 00:48:29.468
That’s just as a friend, right?

00:48:29.844 --> 00:48:33.514
Even if he’s the one who’s sick,
I’d do this, too, because he’s my friend.

00:48:36.517 --> 00:48:38.686
Lie down now.

00:48:47.111 --> 00:48:48.195
Kino—

00:48:49.113 --> 00:48:53.659
if you want, you can
sleep here next to me later,

00:48:53.659 --> 00:48:55.327
so you’ll be more comfortable.

00:48:56.120 --> 00:48:57.621
Don’t worry about me.

00:48:58.122 --> 00:49:00.666
Rest and get well, okay?

00:49:03.252 --> 00:49:04.503
Good night, Via.

00:49:07.298 --> 00:49:08.757
Good night, Kino.

00:49:12.636 --> 00:49:13.846
And—

00:49:15.639 --> 00:49:17.224
thank you.

00:49:21.562 --> 00:49:22.605
Good night.

00:49:22.730 --> 00:49:24.064
Sleep now.

00:49:59.433 --> 00:50:00.643
Good morning.

00:50:04.939 --> 00:50:06.774
Your fever’s gone down.

00:50:07.608 --> 00:50:08.692
Have a seat.

00:50:08.817 --> 00:50:10.152
Breakfast is ready.

00:50:14.490 --> 00:50:15.866
I’ll just get some water.

00:50:35.761 --> 00:50:36.679
Take your medicine after you eat.

00:50:36.679 --> 00:50:38.305
Here, some vitamins, too.

00:50:40.516 --> 00:50:42.893
I need to go. We have a
promo schedule later for the movie.

00:50:46.105 --> 00:50:47.731
Thanks. We’ll watch.

00:50:49.483 --> 00:50:51.277
Focus on getting better.

00:50:51.819 --> 00:50:52.736
Okay?

00:50:52.945 --> 00:50:54.029
I’m leaving now.

00:51:48.500 --> 00:51:49.043
Alright.

00:51:49.460 --> 00:51:50.044
Okay.

00:51:52.463 --> 00:51:55.424
We’ll leave soon, too, Kino.
We might be late for the shoot.

00:51:58.510 --> 00:51:59.470
Engineer!

00:51:59.803 --> 00:52:00.554
Hello.

00:52:03.515 --> 00:52:05.976
Ah, Clea, why did you call me “Kino”?

00:52:06.393 --> 00:52:10.022
Sorry, it just stuck because
a while ago you told me

00:52:10.022 --> 00:52:11.940
that was your childhood nickname.

00:52:13.942 --> 00:52:16.945
Actually, it’s only Via
who calls me that.

00:52:16.945 --> 00:52:17.905
Oh.

00:52:18.864 --> 00:52:20.949
Sorry. I didn’t know the context.

00:52:20.949 --> 00:52:21.742
It’s fine.

00:52:21.742 --> 00:52:22.701
Sorry, I’m sorry.

00:52:22.701 --> 00:52:24.953
Okay, let’s go back to “Larkin.”

00:52:26.205 --> 00:52:28.082
Thanks for understanding.

00:52:35.881 --> 00:52:36.548
What?

00:52:36.548 --> 00:52:39.551
You’re slow! I’m even doing
high knees, you know.

00:52:39.593 --> 00:52:40.469
See?

00:52:41.679 --> 00:52:42.638
What have you been eating, dude?

00:52:42.638 --> 00:52:44.390
Are you training for the Olympics?

00:52:44.682 --> 00:52:46.183
Just in a good mood, bro.

00:52:46.642 --> 00:52:47.685
Oh, why?

00:52:49.395 --> 00:52:52.481
Via and I had a serious
talk on Mama’s birthday.

00:52:53.148 --> 00:52:54.858
I think we’re okay now.
We’re friends again.

00:52:55.372 --> 00:52:58.333
- No wonder you’re in top shape, huh.
- Ouch.

00:52:58.362 --> 00:52:59.279
That’s why!

00:52:59.279 --> 00:53:00.572
That’s why I can do more.

00:53:00.572 --> 00:53:01.365
You’re so weak, man.

00:53:01.365 --> 00:53:01.824
See.

00:53:01.824 --> 00:53:04.796
- Wait a bit. Let’s rest first.
- See? Look at me.

00:53:04.821 --> 00:53:07.574
- Damn, you’re so full of yourself.
- Check this.

00:53:07.996 --> 00:53:09.915
- All right, wait!
- So, let’s go already?

00:53:09.915 --> 00:53:11.333
You’re so slow!

00:53:18.315 --> 00:53:20.234
You’ve really grown so much.

00:53:21.176 --> 00:53:22.511
I’m proud of you.

00:53:24.972 --> 00:53:26.348
Hello, guys!

00:53:27.975 --> 00:53:30.519
Is Clea your girlfriend?

00:53:30.978 --> 00:53:32.521
Is Clea my girlfriend?

00:53:32.646 --> 00:53:33.689
Oh, a new question.

00:53:34.106 --> 00:53:37.025
Do I like someone right now?

00:53:38.700 --> 00:53:44.956
♪ An orange sky, painting the beauty— ♪

00:53:45.159 --> 00:53:46.043
Via.

00:53:46.068 --> 00:53:46.861
Kino.

00:53:47.327 --> 00:53:48.620
Say it, Rye.

00:53:50.247 --> 00:53:53.417
I wanna write music, Kino.

00:53:55.627 --> 00:53:58.589
I thought maybe
it wasn’t meant for me.

00:53:58.589 --> 00:54:01.175
That when I start writing a song,

00:54:01.398 --> 00:54:04.970
I might realize that
I’m not good at it either.

00:54:12.478 --> 00:54:14.688
Via, let’s eat lunch
first before we leave.

00:54:14.772 --> 00:54:16.690
- Oh, Avi!
- Uncle Arkin!

00:54:16.857 --> 00:54:18.108
You’re here!

00:54:18.108 --> 00:54:19.234
Give me a hug.

00:54:19.234 --> 00:54:20.170
Here.

00:54:23.071 --> 00:54:25.324
Uncle Arkin, once you’re famous,

00:54:25.324 --> 00:54:27.493
you can’t join your
loved ones to eat anymore?

00:54:27.868 --> 00:54:31.955
Arkin, is it true that you and Clea
are building a house together?